                                 taxonomyUri="uddi:systinet.com:soa:model:taxonomies:qualityFeature"
                                 value="usability"/>
            </g:qualityFeatureGroup>
            <p:rationale>Requesting a password for each application on the ICT system once a user has logged on is not user friendly and very inefficient. Therefore, once all applications have sufficient direct access to a basic level of authentication, it is important to let users log on all at once.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>There is a standard feature available to authenticate users. Applications are associated with the standard authentication facility so that they do not have to ask for an additional authentication. Applications that a higher level of security questions ask an additional authentication. It is affiliated with federated authentication services in the chain so that single log is also possible beyond the boundaries of the organization.</p:implications>
